result.execSummary:
The defendant Amy Catherine Asleson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 10:41 am case called. Defendant Amy Catherine Asleson in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Statement by ADA Anderson and makes statement regarding counsel. Court questions defendant regarding counsel. 10:49 am case recalled, same appearances.   Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea:  No Contest to Count 1. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court sentences the defendant to: 4 days WCJ, with 3 days credit. Time served sentence. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. No DNA sample to be provided but surcharge to be paid. Appeal Rights Given.
from Defendant Re: Request to Amend Bond Conditions

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.

Case called @ 1:18 p.m. Defendant Amy Catherine Asleson in court, in custody, appears via video.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Atty Zouski appears on unpaid financial obligations.   Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel. Defendant will be privately retaining counsel. DA Blader requesting $500 Cash Bond. No statement by DE regarding bond. Court orders $500 Cash Bond. NGP entered.   STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.

Unpaid financial obligations - Statement by Atty Zouski- DE owes $776.10 on unpaid fines and forfeitures. The court finds contempt. Court orders - 30 days WCJ - Purge conditions: $776.10 for release from custody. 

  Status conference scheduled for October 20, 2015 at 10:45 am.

All Cases Called @ 3:25 PM: Defendant Amy Catherine Asleson not in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Riverside Ruling in favor of the State.  In light of nonappearance, Arrest Warrant authorized with Statewide Extradition.  Default Judgment ordered as to companion citations in 2015TR000010; 2015TR000011, 2015TR000012 and 2015TR000013 with bond amounts noted on the citations.
